🕵️ Time-Jam (Working Title)
📖 Overview

This project is a 2D isometric mystery game where players must solve a procedurally generated case within a strict time limit.

Players explore dynamically generated rooms, uncover clues, and complete time-sensitive objectives in order to solve the mystery before time runs out. Every playthrough is designed to be unique through the use of grammar-driven generation systems.

🎮 Core Concept
You are placed in a mystery scenario with limited time.
The world is generated dynamically based on narrative rules.
Objectives must be completed at specific times or conditions.
Failure to solve the mystery before time expires results in a game over.

🔑 Key Features (Planned)

⏳ Time-Based Gameplay
Global countdown timer drives urgency.
Certain actions and objectives are only available at specific times.
Missed opportunities can lock the player out of solving the mystery.

🧩 Procedural Mystery Generation
Mysteries are generated using a grammar-based system.
Objectives, clues, and events are dynamically created.
Each run produces a different sequence of events.

🏠 Dynamic Room Generation
Rooms are generated based on the outcome of the grammar system.
Layouts adapt to the current mystery scenario.
Exploration is a core mechanic tied to uncovering clues.

🧠 Objective System
Objectives are not static.
Tasks are generated and scheduled dynamically.
Players must interpret and act on clues to determine what to do and when.

🎨 2D Isometric Perspective
Game is presented in a 2D isometric view.
Emphasis on spatial exploration and environmental storytelling.

